gomodel:SYNGO_4170  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: dSTORM imaging of granule cell synapses with the dendritic spines of Purkinje cells show co-localization of mGlur4 microdomains with Munc18-1 (Fig 5) and Bassoon (Fig 4).\n\nantibody KO verified: monoclonal mouse antibody against Munc18-1 (catalog no. 116011) were from Synaptic Systems (Göttingen, Germany).\n\n28/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper shows that mGlur4 closely associates with active zone marker Bassoon. It also shows that Munc18-1 is localised with mGlur4.\nSynGO ID:82 (PMID:17110441) shows that Munc18-1 plays an essential role in synaptic vesicle priming. Based on all these, the term \"presynaptic active zone cytoplasmic component\".. Experimental description: M&M: Wildtype adult FVB mice" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4170" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

